EXPERIMENT 8 
Develop a query to demonstrate Text search using catalog data collection for a given 
word  
This demonstrates how to perform text search on a catalog collection. 
● First, product data is inserted into the collection. 
● Then, a text index is created on the description field to enable searching. 
● Finally, the $text query is used to search for a specific word (e.g., "gaming"). 
_______________________________________________________________ 

sample data 
db.catalog.insertMany([ 
{ name: "Laptop", description: "Good for gaming" }, 
{ name: "Mouse", description: "Gaming device" }, 
{ name: "Chair", description: "Office furniture" } 
]) 
Create text index 
db.catalog.createIndex({ description: "text" }) 
Text search query (for word "gaming") 
db.catalog.find( {  $text: { $search: "gaming" } }) 
